:The figures you cite are incorrect, per [http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/IS.AIR.PSGR the source] you provided. Under the Indonesia section of the source, it states 2006-2010 was 88,594,513 and that 2011-2015 was 94,504,086. There is no 2009 bracket in the source; the 2006-2010 bracket is the closest to it. As such I have modified the article to reflect what the source states. Perhaps you have another source that backs up the figures you provide, because the one you cite does not. I have rewritten this content in the lead to read as follows below. <span class="smallcaps" style="font-variant:small-caps;">[[User:Northamerica1000|North America]]<sup>[[User talk:Northamerica1000|<font size="-2">1000</font>]]</sup></span> 09:21, 14 December 2015 (UTC)
<blockquote>In 2006-2010 the number of Indonesia's air passengers was 88,594,513, and between 2011-2015 the number of passengers was 94,504,086.</blockquote>
:: No.. no.., you read the column incorrectly, the figure 88,594,513 is located in the 2013 column (the blue-greyish bold year ones), not the 2006-2010 which is actually a link to that period (years span). Okay.., let me guide you step by step on how to access the World Bank data on specific year, look at this link: [http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/IS.AIR.PSGR] now click the 2006-2010 section and the screen will show this page:[http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/IS.AIR.PSGR?page=1] follow the column 2009 to Indonesia and you will find the figure: 27,421,235. The figure between 2009 and 2014 shows a tremendous change which is more than three folds. <span style="background:white;color:blue;font:arialbold;border-radius:4px"><b>&nbsp;''[[User:Gunkarta|Gunkarta]]''&nbsp;</b></span><span style="background:lightblue;color:blue;border-radius:2px">&nbsp;''[[User talk:Gunkarta|talk]]''&nbsp;</span> 11:54, 14 December 2015 (UTC)
